This is my comfort pizza, growing up in MPLS it was the pizza of choice. I can honestly say not much has changed. The pizza is the same and oh so good, the atmosphere is just a home town pizza place, the attached bar, is a bar. Service is quick and simple. I will always go back.

I don't get it. This is like Chicago tavern style pizza with way too much cheese and very little seasonings.  It's very, fine, I guess?

I'm guessing this is immensely popular because it was what people grew up with around here, but you'd be better off buying some decent dough from somewhere and making a homemade pizza.
